---
/**
 * conduct/index.astro — Code of Conduct
 * Route: /conduct/
 *
 * Content migrated verbatim from legacy site:
 * https://bcc.bhopal.info/code-of-conduct/
 * Last updated on legacy site: June 12, 2026.
 *
 * Migration rules followed:
 * - Content imported exactly — no rewrites, no omissions, no additions.
 * - BaseLayout used (provides SiteHeader + SiteFooter).
 * - V3 typography and spacing tokens applied.
 * - No shared components modified.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/ui/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Code of Conduct"
  description="Behavioral rules, field safety regulations, and wildlife preservation ethics for all BCC members."
>

  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Code of Conduct"
    subtitle="Behavioral rules, field safety regulations, and wildlife preservation ethics for all BCC members."
    meta="Last updated: June 12, 2026"
  />

  <!-- Body -->
  <section class="policy-section" aria-label="Code of Conduct">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="policy-document">

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h2 id="section-1">1. Purpose &amp; Core Values</h2>
          <p>Bhopal Camera Club is a registered educational and artistic community. We exist to celebrate the art of photography in an environment that is safe, respectful, and ethically responsible. This Code of Conduct applies to all digital interactions (on our platform, forums, and groups) as well as offline events (photowalks, workshops, and exhibitions).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h2 id="section-2">2. Interactive &amp; Online Conduct</h2>
          <p>We are dedicated to providing a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of skill level, gender, race, or background:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Constructive Critique Only:</strong> Criticize the photograph, not the photographer. Keep feedback respectful, technical, and creative.</li>
            <li><strong>Zero Tolerance for Harassment:</strong> Offensive remarks, personal attacks, intimidation, or unwelcome advances in online groups or offline walks will result in immediate membership revocation.</li>
            <li><strong>No Self-Promotion Spam:</strong> Sharing external commercial links, non-photography business ads, or unsolicited promotional requests is prohibited.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h2 id="section-3">3. Photowalk Safety &amp; Field Rules</h2>
          <p>When participating in outdoor photowalks:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Always follow the coordinator's safety instructions and local laws.</li>
            <li>Maintain a clean field footprint. Do not litter, vandalize heritage monuments, or destroy local flora.</li>
            <li>Respect local communities. Always ask for permission before shooting portraits of street vendors, children, or private residences. If someone objects, delete the photo immediately.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h2 id="section-4">4. Wildlife &amp; Nature Conservation Ethics</h2>
          <p>BCC takes pride in documenting Bhopal's rich biodiversity. We enforce strict ethical rules for wildlife and nature photography. The welfare of the subject must always take precedence over obtaining the photograph:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Strict Prohibition on Nest Baiting:</strong> Under no circumstances may a member use live or artificial bait, play audio playback calls, or clear vegetation around nests to capture photos. Such practices stress parents and expose vulnerable chicks to predators.</li>
            <li><strong>Safe Distance:</strong> Maintain an evolutionarily responsible distance. If an animal exhibits signs of distress (flight response, warning calls, changes in behavior), back away slowly.</li>
            <li><strong>No Flash or Artificial Disturbances:</strong> Do not use bright flash triggers on nocturnal animals or birds of prey, nor disturb animals during hibernation or mating seasons.</li>
            <li><strong>Monsoon Nesting Safety:</strong> Exercise extra caution during the monsoon nesting cycles. Avoid nesting zones in Van Vihar and surrounding reserve forests.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h2 id="section-5">5. Enforcement &amp; Violations</h2>
          <p>Violations of this Code of Conduct can be reported confidentially to the club coordinators. The core council reserves the right to suspend or permanently expel any member found violating these ethical standards, without refund of registration fees.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Policy Section ── */
.policy-section {
  background: var(--surface-1);
  padding: var(--s-8) 0 var(--s-12);
}

/* ── Policy Document ── */
.policy-document {
  max-width: 760px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--s-6);
}

/* ── Policy Block ── */
.policy-block {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  padding-top: var(--s-4);
}
.policy-block h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-h3);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--ink-900);
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
}
.policy-block p {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  font-size: var(--text-body);
  color: var(--ink-600);
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
}
.policy-block p:last-child {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}
.policy-block ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: var(--s-1) 0 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--s-2);
}
.policy-block ul li {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  font-size: var(--text-body);
  color: var(--ink-600);
  line-height: 1.65;
  padding-left: var(--s-3);
  position: relative;
}
.policy-block ul li::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  top: 11px;
  width: 5px;
  height: 1px;
  background: var(--gold-500);
}

/* ── Responsive ── */
@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .policy-section {
    padding: var(--s-6) 0 var(--s-8);
  }
}
</style>

<script>
  import { loadPageHero } from '../../lib/hero-loader';
  loadPageHero('conduct');
</script>
